    <h3 itemprop="headline">A woman's hypothermia death in Pittsburgh after her release from ICE custody is ruled a homicide</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      The death of a woman from Haiti seeking asylum in the U.S. who died from hypothermia days after her release from federal custody was ruled a homicide by a Pennsylvania county medical examiner's office.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/us/2026/06/13/a-womans-hypothermia-death-in-pittsburgh-after-her-release-from-ice-custody-is-ruled-a-homicide/"  >(Jack Dura, Associated Press, Local 4)</a>
    </p>
