        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Why I&#8217;m leaving Copilot for Gemini</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      I’ve been using and writing about Microsoft Copilot since it was publicly released in 2023. I’ve reviewed it, written articles about using it more effectively, explained how to curb hallucinations in it and other similar tools, and detailed how to use it in concert with Microsoft 365.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2026/06/10/why-im-leaving-copilot-for-gemini/"  >(Computer World)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
</div><div class="column text"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Mon, 08 Jun 2026 12:29:31 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Mon, 08 Jun 2026 12:29:31 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Info World">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static14/tech/2026/06/08/google-protocol-buffers-flaw-turns-schemas-into-shells-2.webp" alt="Protocol Buffers schemas expose remote code execution risk" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Protocol Buffers schemas expose remote code execution risk</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      A widely used JavaScript implementation of Google’s Protocol Buffers format is placing too much trust in untrusted data, exposing affected applications to remote code execution and other attacks.
Researchers at Cyera have disclosed six vulnerabilities affecting “protobuf.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2026/06/08/google-protocol-buffers-flaw-turns-schemas-into-shells-2/"  >(Info World)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Thu, 11 Jun 2026 09:00:00 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Thu, 11 Jun 2026 09:00:00 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Info World">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static14/tech/2026/06/11/build-an-agent-sell-an-agent.webp" alt="Build an agent? Sell an agent" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Build an agent? Sell an agent</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      Modern AI systems have evolved beyond the simple chatbots that quickly became popular. Now they use semantic tools to manage workflows and link machines to machines, providing a flexible and effective framework for the next generation of business automation.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2026/06/11/build-an-agent-sell-an-agent/"  >(Info World)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
